This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a feature-based approach to time series classification that uses a database of algorithms to extract thousands of interpretable features from time series. Additionally, the paper uses a linear classifier and greedy forward feature selection to select the most informative features for classification. 

The paper also involves data mining (cs.DM) as it involves extracting features from time series data and using them for classification. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves using machine learning techniques to classify time series data. 

Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves extracting features from time series data to understand the properties of the data set, which can guide further scientific investigation. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing time series data to understand the properties of the data set.
